Generate a comprehensive pre-call sales briefing for a Helios Marketing
sales rep about to call this real estate brokerage. Use ONLY facts present
in the intel and conversation history below — do not invent details.

The briefing must be markdown. Use the exact section structure shown below.
Be specific. Be useful. A rep should be able to read this in 90 seconds and
walk into the call prepared.

HELIOS KNOWLEDGE BASE (reference for accurate talking points, services,
pricing ranges, and proof points):
{{ knowledge_base }}

LEAD INTEL:
{{ intel | tojson(indent=2) }}

LEAD METADATA:
- Company: {{ lead.company }}
- City: {{ lead.city }}
- Contact: {{ lead.owner_name or "Unknown" }}
- Email: {{ lead.email }}
- Phone: {{ lead.phone or "Not on file" }}
- Google Rating: {{ lead.google_rating }} stars ({{ lead.google_reviews }} reviews)

CONVERSATION HISTORY:
{% for msg in thread %}
--- {{ msg.direction | upper }} {% if msg.sent_at %}({{ msg.sent_at }}){% endif %} ---
{% if msg.subject %}Subject: {{ msg.subject }}{% endif %}
{{ msg.body }}
{% endfor %}

REQUIRED SECTIONS (use these exact headers in this exact order):

# Pre-Call Briefing: {{ lead.company }}

## Contact
- Name, title, email, phone in a tight block.

## Company Snapshot
A 4-6 sentence paragraph covering: what they do, who they serve, how big
they are, what makes them distinctive. Pulled entirely from intel.

## What We Know About Their Pain
Bullet list of specific signals from the conversation about what's not
working for them, what they're frustrated by, or what they're trying to
achieve. If the conversation is short, infer from intel where reasonable
but mark inferences as "(inferred)".

## Recommended Talking Points
Three numbered talking points the rep should bring up. Each one should
reference a specific detail from the intel or conversation, not generic
sales talking points.

## How They Came In
Brief analysis of which hook tier landed in the original cold email and
why it likely worked. Reference the specific phrase used as the hook.
Pull this from the first OUTBOUND message in the thread (which has
hook_tier_used and hook_text fields in messages table — though those
aren't in this prompt context, infer from the body).

## Open Questions
Bullet list of 2-4 questions the rep should ask on the call to qualify
further, gather missing intel, or move toward a close.

## Risks & Watch-Outs
Bullet list of any red flags or things to be careful about. Examples:
competitor mentions, budget concerns raised, timeline pressure.
If none, write "None apparent from available intel."

Do NOT include any preamble, meta-commentary, or "here is your briefing"
text. Output the markdown document directly starting with the H1.
